author: Tom Lowrey
title: Zero Canberra coronavirus cases might not be the end — it might not even mean the end is near
description: The ACT may soon have no known cases of the virus within its borders, but the Chief Minister says the city is a long way from returning to life as usual.
content:
Posted 
April 23, 2020 08:13:12
Within a fortnight, the ACT may achieve a feat few thought likely only a month ago.
It could become Australia's first jurisdiction to record zero active cases of COVID-19 within its borders.
